{"disposition":"accepted","experiment_id":"WM-001","findings":[{"id":"F001","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"The terminal v1.14 failure is confined to the independent archive reader's second-iterator exhaustion defect: all declared members had verified, the archive had no membership delta, the failed binding was outer-finalized, no formal launch occurred, and no v1.14 outcome or evidence can authorize v1.15."},{"id":"F002","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"The independent archive reader now retains one iterator through declared-member verification and exhaustion. A production-writer multi-member USTAR traverses both the central and independent real readers with identical retained bytes, while one shared stale-member-digest mutation is rejected by both."},{"id":"F003","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"Central and independent archive semantics are rooted in the archived producer manifest, enforce its exact field set and real ordered canonical UTC timestamps, require the exact one-level nine-role evidence namespace, and reject undeclared, reordered, duplicated, linked, noncanonical, changed, truncated, padded, trailing, or physical-extra members."},{"id":"F004","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"Archive construction rejects unsafe or colliding evidence names before insertion, including backslash and producer-namespace collisions, and both readers enforce per-member and aggregate retained-payload limits plus stable regular-file, single-link, and canonical archive custody."},{"id":"F005","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"Both captured bootstraps and every producer, result, audit, reproduction, runtime, invocation, and stderr role are digest-joined to the corresponding archived member. Real producer/audit-to-closure authorization helpers reject each archived/live role substitution."},{"id":"F006","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"Coverage claims are correctly bounded: the shared archive test uses both unmocked archive readers; the producer/audit fixture traverses the real closure authorization helpers; separate complete qualification and formal-input fixtures cover the semantic consumers. The active protocol, plan, architecture, READMEs, and runbook do not claim a single fully unmocked closure-to-formal-lineage fixture."},{"id":"F007","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"Preformal, binding, launch, archived-producer, authorization, and formal-input boundaries use strict JSON scalar identity and exact field sets, so boolean, integer, and floating aliases, incomplete identities, malformed receipts, and self-vouching or mismatched references cannot authorize execution."},{"id":"F008","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"All ten preformal commands preserve separate stdout/stderr custody and require exact byte-empty stderr in generation, canonical verification, preserved/bound projection, independent verification, and protocol expectations."},{"id":"F009","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"Fresh v1.15 derivation regenerates 10 unique current masters and 1,360 unique current streams and compares them with 140 prior masters and 19,040 prior streams through v1.14; every internal and cross-domain master/stream collision class is zero."},{"id":"F010","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"Scientific continuity is preserved: all 17 canonical scientific protocol blocks and the model, learning, planning, and runtime-lane kernel bytes match v1.14; formal-binding v10, raw-result v9, protocol representation v9, and preformal representation v2 remain unchanged."},{"id":"F011","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"Fresh canonical QA and runtime environments were rebuilt non-editably from one corrected wheel. Their Prospect 0.0.1 distribution digest is identical (b654735d72d4d36db2244f45a346f7ba9e9c3309a830cc23e503370c2bd89202), the runtime excludes QA tools, and its exact 45-row installed closure verifies against the regenerated lock."},{"id":"F012","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"The runbook mechanically regenerates and verifies the protocol/schema seal, binds an independently authored prospective review to the staged implementation manifest, names valid test nodes, applies the decisive archive and authorization regressions before evidence, and preserves single-use development, binding, launch, audit, and adjudication custody."},{"id":"F013","resolution":"informational","severity":"note","summary":"The assurance boundary remains explicit: repository, environment, path, filesystem, base-interpreter, kernel, and cooperative-lock integrity are trusted; hashes and same-inode custody do not provide external attestation or resistance to a same-principal, privileged, compromised-kernel, or mutate-and-restore adversary."}],"implementation_files":[{"bytes":1638,"path":"Makefile","sha256":"142152df3f1f9e5531374c96379db91f65d5dbe12182b89a9156b1f8bc504338"},{"bytes":148,"path":"bench/__init__.py","sha256":"6c7b9de75c247ced5f62064f9786cf6e2f14d958bd1be6eb65c6ed69680b6942"},{"bytes":561,"path":"bench/epistemic/__init__.py","sha256":"bb77dc8aba3b32b6bc2df16a5abd9fc24b0ece2a389e814c3337a0f637a5467e"},{"bytes":44718,"path":"bench/epistemic/lifecycle.py","sha256":"3d30d947ca830a0c307f2e7f40d31bc4bef51d497f2e96d68f000fa864e3ed25"},{"bytes":30661,"path":"bench/epistemic/maturity.py","sha256":"2a81abe60f12285f66f2bcd351589de28851412f1d9df7f2003843a845a2510e"},{"bytes":13611,"path":"bench/epistemic/problem.py","sha256":"c66ae13d3e833ffd1be1562a89e0e9035d6197b95723179b930c1ca2a1059c66"},{"bytes":1097,"path":"bench/epistemic/run_maturity.py","sha256":"86ae2c3175262f559a274827c96c30212fbdb9250e3a4614f92c861b7498feb7"},{"bytes":20656,"path":"bench/epistemic/runtime_lane.py","sha256":"d8f0c7a85be786c3a813ee1f169abcbc2791a642e46fba5978f7a1140cc50387"},{"bytes":278,"path":"bench/world_model_lifecycle/SEALED_PROTOCOL.